<dl id="n05013g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05013g">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05013g"> 13(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Heva (Living)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"> &ldquo;When the dual idea expressed in the name was forgotten,&rdquo; he adds, &ldquo;Adam became the Great Father, the Great Mother receiving the name of Eve (<mark><i>Havvah</i>), i.e., living, or life</mark>, although Adam in the generic sense of &lsquo;Mankind&rsquo; denotes both male and female.&rdquo; <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [The Creation Story] 22</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
